fields.name: Learn more about Eco points
fields.value:
**To check how many points you have:** enter the command `!points` in the section #check-your-points
**How to send Eco points:** enter the command
`!send @username number comment`
**How to earn Eco points:**
1. Compete in bounties in #content-bounties and do activities in #points-bartering
2. Participate in discussions in #general, #eco-nomics, and elsewhere
3. Follow the channels, participate in conversations and contests
4. Invite people to the project and they can thank you in the #invite-thank-yous section. Only users with a large number of invitees will get points
5. Create original (without vulgarity) memes in the #meme-lab section6. Generally be helpful to the project and help the community learn and grow together!

Hi everyone, I want to introduce to you a very nice tool for translation called Crowdin. Crowdin is a cloud-based solution created to support multilingual translations. It is trusted by various projects including Ethereum and Aavegotchi. On their website, they state that they are trusted by big tech companies such as Jet Brains, Git Lab, Avast, Raspberry, and Mojang. From my personal view, it has many advantages: - Easy to access and start: you don't need to need to know about coding. Just simply register with your email, receive an invitation link, and start translating - Effective management: it is super easy to monitor the progress of every language, and its big or small sections - Optimal support for the best translation experience: + You can translate all the document at once or one part at a time + For parts that require coding such as , you just need to click on the buttons containing them and they will appear on your translation. + It has an AI to remind you of double space or the additional marks + It has a QA section right on your translations to help you evaluate your own + It gives you preference from the global data. For example: "there are 96% of translations translated this word to "daddy". Besides, it also offers preference from other languages so you can compare it. + You can even search for the words that you don't know how to translate properly + It highlights the words or phrases that have not been done + You can search the sections if you need + You can switch between parts with only the keyboards - It can sync to Github if you put your documents there - It offers free plans but you can pay to get more excellent features which can be checked here: https://crowdin.com/pricing#crowdin-pricing-key-features Cons: - Sometimes the moderation of old texts can affect the format and you will have to fill the translation again but you just need one click to do that

You can have multiple suggestions to one string by various people, then you select the best one or the one you think is more fitting.
